Wait, let me recheck the Java code: In Java, for each "temp1, temp2" pair:

if (H[temp1 - 1] < H[temp2 - 1]) then ans[temp1 - 1] = false;

Else if H[temp1-1] > ... set the temp2-1 ans to false. Else set both to false. So in Fortran's 1-based array, H(temp1) corresponds to H[temp1-1] in Java.
